# function to graph by using for loop
In [14]:
def f(playerlist):
    for name in playerlist:
        plt.plot(Games[Pdict[name]],c='black',ls='--',marker='*',ms=7,label=name)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left',bbox_to_anchor=(1,1))
    plt.xticks(list(range(0,10)),Seasons,rotation='vertical')#change the title of the graph
    plt.show()

#advanced function to change color and marker and fix input
In [17]:
def f(data,playerlist=Players):
    col={'KobeBryant':'black','JoeJohnson':'red','LeBronJames':'green','CarmeloAnthony':'blue','DwightHoward':'magenta','ChrisBosh':'black','ChrisPaul':'red','KevinDurant':'green','DerrickRose':'blue','DwayneWade':'magenta'}
    Mrk={'KobeBryant':'s','JoeJohnson':'o','LeBronJames':'.','CarmeloAnthony':'1','DwightHoward':'2','ChrisBosh':'p','ChrisPaul':'+','KevinDurant':'D','DerrickRose':'d','DwayneWade':'*'}
    for name in playerlist:
        plt.plot(Games[Pdict[name]],c=col[name],ls='--',marker=Mrk[name],ms=7,label=name)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left',bbox_to_anchor=(1,1))
    plt.xticks(list(range(0,10)),Seasons,rotation='vertical')#change the title of the graph
    plt.show()
